@*
    Help.cshtml - Help documentation view for PcApprovalAction component
    Provides user documentation about the approval action buttons component
*@

<h4>Approval Action Component</h4>

<p>
    This component renders <strong>approve</strong>, <strong>reject</strong>, and <strong>delegate</strong> 
    buttons for processing approval requests. These action buttons allow authorized approvers to take 
    action on pending approval requests within a workflow.
</p>

<h5>How It Works</h5>
<p>
    Clicking each button opens a modal dialog for entering comments before submitting the action. 
    This ensures that all approval decisions are documented with appropriate context.
</p>

<h5>Available Actions</h5>
<dl>
    <dt><strong>Approve</strong></dt>
    <dd>
        Advances the request to the next step in the approval workflow. If this is the final step, 
        the request is marked as fully approved and the workflow completes successfully.
    </dd>
    
    <dt><strong>Reject</strong></dt>
    <dd>
        Marks the request as rejected. A reason for rejection is required in the comments field. 
        Once rejected, the workflow terminates and the source record's approval status is updated accordingly.
    </dd>
    
    <dt><strong>Delegate</strong></dt>
    <dd>
        Allows reassigning the approval request to another user. The delegatee becomes responsible 
        for taking the approval action. This is useful when the original approver is unavailable 
        or when the request requires input from someone with different expertise.
    </dd>
</dl>

<h5>Configuration Options</h5>
<dl>
    <dt><code>request_id</code></dt>
    <dd>
        <strong>Required.</strong> Data source binding for the approval request ID. Use a data source 
        expression like <code>{{Record.id}}</code> to bind to a record property from the page context. 
        This identifies which approval request the action buttons will operate on.
    </dd>
</dl>

<h5>Usage Notes</h5>
<ul>
    <li>Action buttons are only enabled when the request status is "pending".</li>
    <li>The current user must be an authorized approver for the current workflow step to see enabled buttons.</li>
    <li>All actions are recorded in the approval history for audit purposes.</li>
    <li>Email notifications are sent to relevant parties when actions are taken.</li>
</ul>


